\lang1033\b\f1\fs16 White to play\lang1042\b0\f0\fs18
\lang1033\f1\fs16 How should White capture Black when Black seems to have a good amount of eye space?

\lang1042\f0\fs18
])
(;AW[ro][so][op][pp][qp][oq][or][os]AB[rp][pq][qq][pr][sr][qs]
;W[rq]
;B[rr]
;W[sp]
;B[ps]LB[rq:1][rr:2][sp:3][ps:4]C[Dia.1 Endgame moves

If you cut with White 1 and take a Black stone then you are simply playing endgame moves and are not succeeding in capturing Black.  Black lives with 4.
\lang1042\f1\fs18

])
(;AW[ro][so][op][pp][qp][oq][or][os]AB[rp][pq][qq][pr][sr][qs]
;W[rr]
;B[rq]
;W[sp]
;B[rs]LB[rr:1][rq:2][sp:3][rs:4]C[Dia.2 Alive in matbogi?

What about the placement attack of White 1?  Actually, this is a severe move.  The only thing Black can do is play 2.  Now is an important moment!

If White thinks Black lives in matbogi then he'll play 3 and Black will play  and live with two eyes.  Can you think of a better place to play than White 3?
\lang1042\f1\fs18
